<subSubSection id="D23CFFB372951CC63BC89880C69B18B5" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="FFFAE10CCA370692B886759B0837DB7A" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B67571BC6A6DCB4B899336E50A0E7A7D" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
This species is second in size only to 
<taxonomicName id="C4CD99EA293FDDFC3ECC50C0FFC19DCE" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Baconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Baconia loricata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loricata">Baconia loricata</taxonomicName>
, but is still significantly smaller than that species. It may be further distinguished by its lack of transverse propygidial stria, densely punctate frons, and elongate legs, particularly the protibia (Figs 9
<normalizedToken id="9C36B00CB6BD4C165538268DB1F48048" originalValue="A–D">A-D</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
